# Tic-Tac-Toe

A simple command-line Tic-Tac-Toe game implemented in Python.

## Features
- Two-player mode
- Simple console interface
- Automatic board clearing for better visuals
- Input validation to prevent invalid moves
- Replay option after game completion

## How to Play
1. Run the script in a Python environment.
2. Players take turns choosing a position (1-9) to place their mark (X or O).
3. The game checks for a winner or a draw after each move.
4. The game announces the winner or declares a draw if the board is full.
5. Players can choose to replay after a game ends.

## Installation & Execution
1. Clone this repository or download the script.
   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/tic-tac-toe.git
   cd tic-tac-toe
   ```
2. Run the script with Python:
   ```sh
   python tic_tac_toe.py
   ```

## Game Controls
- Enter a number between 1-9 to place your move.
- The positions correspond to the board as follows:
  ```
  1 | 2 | 3
  ---------
  4 | 5 | 6
  ---------
  7 | 8 | 9
  ```
- Enter "yes" to replay or "no" to quit after a game ends.

## Requirements
- Python 3.x

